@flexiarg aif/no-self-certification
@title No Self-Certification (A Verdict Moves Only on Evidence Its Maker Did Not Manufacture)
@sigils [⊘/⟲]
@keywords self-certification, circular evidence, prior-equals-value, independence tag, censored observation, calibration, verdict, structural enforcement, untagged-never-counts
@audience anyone building a measurement, calibration, gate, certifier, or reward channel
@tone foundational
@style pattern

! conclusion: A measurement / verdict apparatus must never be moveable by evidence it manufactured itself. Enforce this STRUCTURALLY — with tags the apparatus cannot fake (independence, measured-vs-fallback, settled-vs-transient) and a verdict that counts only those tags — not by vigilance.

  + context: You are building an instrument that issues a verdict — "calibrated", "passed",
    "admissible", "rewardable" — from evidence that the same system also produces, stages, or
    scores. The verdict will look earned long before it is.

  + IF:
      An instrument issues a verdict from evidence it also produces or stages (a calibrator over
      its own predictions, a gate over its own outputs, a reward channel over its own scores).

  + HOWEVER:
      On first contact with reality, every layer tries to certify ITSELF, and each attempt looks
      rigorous: the forward model scores its own constants (`prior == value`); the evidence reader
      eats its own staging files; the realised channel copies predicted on success (a censored
      0.0); the calibration clears on degenerate volume. Vigilance cannot catch these — an
      instrument's *first* catches are about itself, and no human watches every path.

  + THEN:
      Require that a verdict may be moved ONLY by evidence the verdict-maker did not manufacture.
      Tag every evidence record at birth with the properties the apparatus cannot fake —
      `:independent?` (was there an out-of-band witness?), source (`:measured` vs
      `:target-absent-fallback`), settledness (`:settled` vs `:transient`) — and have the verdict
      count ONLY the records whose tags clear. Strictness default: **untagged never counts**.

  + BECAUSE:
      Circularity is invisible from inside the loop precisely because every internal reading is
      consistent with every other — that is what `prior == value` means. The only thing that breaks
      it is a referent the maker had no hand in: an external witness, a settled re-read of a world
      it does not control, a tag it cannot forge. Structure survives where vigilance fails, and it
      converts "be careful" (unauditable) into "the tag is absent, so it does not count" (checkable).

  + canonical-instance:
      The FutonZero G-SIM calibration arc (WM-pilot, 2026-06-11): four distinct self-certification
      attempts surfaced live — censored fallback, transient spike, `prior == value`, and
      operator-gate-as-fruit — each caught only because an independence/source/settled tag existed
      to exclude it, and each then encoded as a permanent structural guard. See
      `[[M-the-perfect-crime]]` (the forensic framing: the crime relocates to a scarcer witness;
      this pattern is the structural half of that ladder) and the reward-red-team fixture
      (the executable suite of the shapes).

  + how-to-apply:
      Before trusting any "it passed", ask: did this verdict move on evidence the system made?
      If yes, find the un-manufactured referent (external witness / settled read / out-of-band
      tag) and gate the verdict on it. If there is none, the verdict is decoration. Minted from the
      arc that learned it, WM-pilot 2026-06-11 (arc-2 cycle 13).
